<div class="help">
  <h1>Help: Wiki</h1>
  <p>Danbooru uses a custom wiki engine with minimal functionality. All formatting is done via <a href="http://hobix.com/textile">Textile</a> (specifically through the SuperRedCloth library).</p>
  <p>To create an internal wiki link, wrap the title in two sets of square brackets. <code>[[Like this]]</code>. You can also create an alias, <code>[[real link|like this]]</code>.</p>
  
  <div class="section">
    <h4>Style Guideline</h4>
    <p>The Danbooru wiki has no specific style guide, but here's some general advice for creating wiki pages for tags:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Use h4 for all headers, h6 for subheaders.</li>
      <li>Bundle any relevant links at the end under a <strong>See also</strong> section.</li>
      <li>For artists, include the artist's home page under the <strong>See also</strong> section</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>
